about.description:
Phi_K is a new and practical correlation coefficient based on several
refinements to Pearson's hypothesis test of independence of two variables.

name: phik
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "PhiK" %}
{% set version = "0.9.8" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/KaveIO/{{ name }}/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e10e0ca0108dc069d597b8629efee717842fd93250cf7912a7a49fd2a5f32897

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - phik_trial = phik.entry_points:phik_trial  # [win]
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.5
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.5
    - numpy >=1.15.4
    - scipy >=1.1.0
    - pandas >=0.23.4
    - matplotlib >=2.2.3
    - numba >=0.38.1
    - pytest >=4.0.2
    - pytest-pylint >=0.13.0
    - nbconvert >=5.3.1
    - jupyter_client >=5.2.3

test:
  imports:
    - phik

about:
  home: https://github.com/KaveIO/PhiK
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Phi_K correlation analyzer library'

  # The remaining entries in this section are optional, but recommended.
  description: |
    Phi_K is a new and practical correlation coefficient based on several
    refinements to Pearson's hypothesis test of independence of two variables.
  doc_url: http://phik.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/KaveIO/PhiK

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - philip-khor
